  "prompt": "What is origin of \"Nehru\" surname?",
  "response": "The surname \"Nehru\" originates from Kashmir, and it is derived from the Persian word \"Nahar\" or \"Nehr,\" which means \"canal\" or \"water channel.\" Historically, the Nehru family was associated with a region near a canal in Kashmir, and this geographical reference became their surname.\n\nThe most famous member of the Nehru family was Jawaharlal Nehru, who became India's first Prime Minister after independence. His father, Motilal Nehru, and subsequent generations were prominent in Indian politics and the independence movement. The family's roots can be traced back to Kashmiri Pandit Brahmins who had traditionally been scholars and administrators.",
